I know. The doctor said that
I can't sing above a G-sharp,

1440
01:30:45.900 --> 01:30:47.265
maybe ever.

1441
01:30:47.944 --> 01:30:51.027
[SOBBING] I thought
the season was over.

1442
01:30:54.992 --> 01:30:57.199
It's okay. It's okay.

1443
01:30:59.497 --> 01:31:02.535
Beca, what do we do?

1444
01:31:12.176 --> 01:31:13.587
I'm sorry.

1445
01:31:14.387 --> 01:31:15.502
Maybe not here.

1446
01:31:16.639 --> 01:31:19.427
All right. Let's
remix this business.

1447
01:31:20.434 --> 01:31:25.019
Aubrey, would you
pick a song for us, please?

1448
01:31:25.106 --> 01:31:27.598
Bruno Mars,
<i>Just The Way You Are.</i>

1449
01:31:29.402 --> 01:31:32.440
Okay. Chloe, are you
okay to take the lead?

1450
01:31:32.530 --> 01:31:33.565
Yeah.

1451
01:31:37.618 --> 01:31:40.201
[VOCALIZING]

1452
01:31:58.723 --> 01:32:04.059
[SINGING POP BALLAD]

1453
01:32:16.115 --> 01:32:18.322
[HARMONIZES WITH R&B SONG]

1454
01:32:33.632 --> 01:32:35.873
[JOINS IN SINGING R&B SONG]

1455
01:33:18.344 --> 01:33:19.334
Hands in.

1456
01:33:23.390 --> 01:33:25.427
[ALL]: One, two...

1457
01:33:25.518 --> 01:33:26.758
[ALL SINGING TOGETHER]
[SINGING LOW NOTE]

1458
01:33:27.228 --> 01:33:28.434
What was that?

1459
01:33:28.521 --> 01:33:30.182
I don't know, I've never
made that sound before.

1460
01:33:30.272 --> 01:33:33.105
Yo, but with your messed up vocal
cords, you could hit the bass notes.

1461
01:33:33.526 --> 01:33:35.187
Do you know what that means?

1462
01:33:35.277 --> 01:33:36.483
Yes, Lilly?

1463
01:33:36.570 --> 01:33:38.686
I think I have something
that can help us out.

1464
01:33:39.907 --> 01:33:42.023
Excuse me, bitch, you
don't need to shout.

1465
01:33:42.201 --> 01:33:44.158
Okay, don't get mouthy.

1466
01:33:46.956 --> 01:33:48.993
[SINGERS VOCALIZING SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

1467
01:33:51.627 --> 01:33:53.584
[PERFORMING VOCAL WARM-UP]

1468
01:33:56.257 --> 01:33:58.749
Ah!

1469
01:33:59.677 --> 01:34:00.963
[JOHN]: <i>Welcome to the finals</i>

1470
01:34:01.053 --> 01:34:04.921
of the 2012 International
Championship of Collegiate A Cappella.

1471
01:34:05.516 --> 01:34:09.100
Lincoln Center is proud to welcome back
all of these young hopefuls tonight

1472
01:34:09.186 --> 01:34:12.804
<i>who are hoping to win a trophy by
making music with their mouths.</i>

1473
01:34:12.898 --> 01:34:14.889
[INAUDIBLE]

1474
01:34:20.614 --> 01:34:23.197
[JOHN]: <i>This is gonna be a big
night, and I tell you, Gail,</i>

1475
01:34:23.325 --> 01:34:26.158
<i>if you can just shut your eyes.</i>
[GAIL]: <i>I'm doing it.</i>

1476
01:34:26.245 --> 01:34:29.363
Shut your eyes and get rid
of all the a-ca-politics,

1477
01:34:29.582 --> 01:34:33.826
<i>then you can remember that being at
Lincoln Center, in the Big Apple,</i>

1478
01:34:33.919 --> 01:34:38.584
<i>and singing on this storied stage is
the dream of every a cappella singer.</i>

1479
01:34:38.674 --> 01:34:40.381
[GAIL]: <i>You said it, John.</i>

1480
01:34:43.846 --> 01:34:47.089
[MAN SINGING GLAM-ROCK SONG]

1481
01:34:47.641 --> 01:34:50.008
[ALL VOCALIZING]

1482
01:34:53.981 --> 01:34:56.018
[AUDIENCE CHEERING]

1483
01:34:56.108 --> 01:35:00.397
<i>The University of Virginia
Hullabahoos, ladies and gentlemen.</i>

1484
01:35:01.405 --> 01:35:02.395
<i>There they are.</i>

1485
01:35:02.489 --> 01:35:04.275
TREBLEMAKERS:
One, two, three, swag!

1486
01:35:04.366 --> 01:35:08.781
[EMCEE]: <i>Welcome back to the International
Championship of Collegiate A Cappella.</i>

1487
01:35:09.413 --> 01:35:14.123
<i>This next group, they need no
introduction, but I'll do it anyway!</i>

1488
01:35:14.210 --> 01:35:15.291
Hey-

1489
01:35:16.670 --> 01:35:17.876
Hey-

1490
01:35:17.963 --> 01:35:18.998
Good luck.

1491
01:35:19.757 --> 01:35:21.873
Thanks. You, too.

1492
01:35:21.967 --> 01:35:24.709
<i>...the Barden University
Treblemakers!</i>

1493
01:35:24.803 --> 01:35:26.965
[AUDIENCE CHEERING]

1494
01:35:33.270 --> 01:35:36.058
[ALL VOCALIZING]

1495
01:35:49.828 --> 01:35:52.286
[SINGING FUNKY R&B SONG]

1496
01:36:50.347 --> 01:36:52.588
[SINGING POP CHORUS]

1497
01:37:20.044 --> 01:37:22.911
[RAPPING HIP-HOP VERSE]

1498
01:37:31.263 --> 01:37:33.470
[VOCALIZING]

1499
01:37:42.191 --> 01:37:44.102
[SINGING POP CHORUS]

1500
01:38:06.507 --> 01:38:08.043
[AUDIENCE CHEERING LOUDLY]

1501
01:38:08.133 --> 01:38:11.046
[GAIL]: <i>Oh, the Trebles closing
it strong like always.</i>

1502
01:38:11.136 --> 01:38:14.925
[JOHN]: <i>Absolutely tight. It's gonna
be very hard to beat that tonight.</i>

1503
01:38:15.015 --> 01:38:17.882
[GAIL]: <i>Every other group has their
work cut out for them, John.</i>

1504
01:38:17.976 --> 01:38:22.061
[JOHN]: <i>I'm glad it's not us anymore, Gail.
Those days are over, thank goodness.</i>

1505
01:38:22.147 --> 01:38:25.230
[GAIL]: <i>Especially since they
wouldn't have us back.</i>

1506
01:38:25.317 --> 01:38:28.730
<i>All right. How about that?</i>

1507
01:38:28.821 --> 01:38:29.936
<i>The Barden University
Treblemakers.</i>

1508
01:38:30.030 --> 01:38:31.111
I love you, awesome nerds.

1509
01:38:31.573 --> 01:38:33.655
Yeah, you guys are the best.

1510
01:38:34.910 --> 01:38:38.995
Even though some of you are pretty thin,
I think that you all have fat hearts,

1511
01:38:39.998 --> 01:38:42.114
and that's what matters.

1512
01:38:42.209 --> 01:38:44.496
Okay, let's just
smash this. Okay?

1513
01:38:44.837 --> 01:38:49.502
[EMCEE]: <i>Ladies and gentlemen,
the Barden Bellas!</i>

1514
01:38:51.510 --> 01:38:54.502
[JOHN]: <i>Oh, my goodness gracious.
Will you look at this?</i>

1515
01:38:54.763 --> 01:38:58.552
<i>Gone are those Bella uniforms and
this is a whole new look for them,</i>

1516
01:38:58.642 --> 01:39:00.303
<i>and it is hot, hot, hot.</i>

1517
01:39:00.394 --> 01:39:02.886
[GAIL]: <i>John, these
girls could turn me.</i>

1518
01:39:07.693 --> 01:39:10.025
[WOMAN]: We love you, Bellas!

1519
01:39:12.114 --> 01:39:13.104
[PLAYS NOTE]

1520
01:39:17.911 --> 01:39:20.699
One, two, three, four.

1521
01:39:21.248 --> 01:39:22.488
[ALL VOCALIZING]

1522
01:39:22.583 --> 01:39:25.496
[SINGING HAPPY POP SONG]

1523
01:39:50.068 --> 01:39:51.399
[VOCALIZING]

1524
01:39:51.487 --> 01:39:53.569
[ALL CONTINUE SINGING]

1525
01:40:15.969 --> 01:40:19.087
[SINGING NEW WAVE LOVE SONG]

1526
01:41:08.480 --> 01:41:10.346
[VOCALIZING]

1527
01:41:15.487 --> 01:41:20.027
[SINGING URBAN DANCE SONG]

1528
01:42:23.055 --> 01:42:25.092
[ALL VOCALIZING]

1529
01:42:34.066 --> 01:42:37.900
[HARMONIZING WITH NEW WAVE LOVE SONG]

1530
01:42:40.447 --> 01:42:42.063
[CONTINUE SINGING URBAN DANCE SONG]

1531
01:42:49.247 --> 01:42:50.954
[SINGING DISCO SONG]

1532
01:42:56.588 --> 01:42:58.170
[AUDIENCE CHEERING WILDLY]

1533
01:43:03.011 --> 01:43:04.501
Way to go, Beca!

1534
01:43:22.114 --> 01:43:23.354
[JOHN]: <i>What a show!</i>

1535
01:43:23.448 --> 01:43:27.567
I think we have just seen some a
cappella history being made, John.

1536
01:43:27.661 --> 01:43:31.529
And from an all-female group, Gail.
I could never have called this one.

1537
01:43:31.623 --> 01:43:34.240
Never. Well, you are
a misogynist at heart,

1538
01:43:34.334 --> 01:43:36.371
so there's no way you would
have bet on these girls to win.

1539
01:43:36.461 --> 01:43:37.451
Absolutely.

1540
01:43:41.133 --> 01:43:43.124
[EMCEE]: <i>Weren't they incredible? Wow!</i>

1541
01:43:45.887 --> 01:43:50.131
<i>Ladies and gentlemen, let's give
it up again for the Barden Bellas!</i>

1542
01:43:52.436 --> 01:43:54.894
Told you. Endings
are the best part.

1543
01:43:54.980 --> 01:43:56.141
You're such a weirdo.

1544
01:44:09.828 --> 01:44:11.614
Listen up, a-ca-ballers.

1545
01:44:11.705 --> 01:44:16.199
I have been rejected by the Army,
shoved into a Dora the Explorer backpack,

1546
01:44:16.293 --> 01:44:19.752
and pushed into the girls' locker
room wearing nothing but suspenders.

1547
01:44:19.838 --> 01:44:22.751
But no matter.
I am in the world that I love.

1548
01:44:23.341 --> 01:44:25.127
And with the assistance
of my boy, Justin...

1549
01:44:25.218 --> 01:44:26.253
My liege-

1550
01:44:26.344 --> 01:44:27.550
I launch this year's auditions.

1551
01:44:29.181 --> 01:44:30.842
Belly roll.
[DRUMMING]

1552
01:44:31.141 --> 01:44:36.727
The most recent ICCA national champion
winners get to pick the audition song.

1553
01:44:36.813 --> 01:44:38.019
[JUSTIN MIMICS CYMBAL CRASHING]

1554
01:44:38.857 --> 01:44:40.518
[WHISPERING]

1555
01:44:43.361 --> 01:44:46.103
All right, nerds.
Let's go with...

1556
01:46:19.958 --> 01:46:21.540
[CHLOE]: Because I have nodes.

1557
01:46:21.626 --> 01:46:25.961
Chloe, don't worry, it's just God
punishing you 'cause you're a ginger.

1558
01:46:27.549 --> 01:46:28.914
[ALL LAUGHING]

